Borrowings by directors and certain officers of M&#38;T and its banking subsidiaries, and by associates of such persons, exclusive of loans aggregating less than $60,000 , amounted to $ 102 million and $ 113 million at December 31, 2022 and 2021, respectively. During 2022 , new borrowings by such persons amounted to $ 7 million (including any borrowings of new directors or officers that were outstanding at the time of their election) and repayments and other reductions (including reductions resulting from individuals ceasing to be directors or officers) were $ 18 million. 

